    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="635"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1489½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">White</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-21">October 21,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Abelli, the Minister of Bolivia, called and I told him I had received his
                    telegram asking us to hold up the cables to Bolivia and Paraguay signed by all
                    the countries of America, but that it had come on Monday morning when everybody
                    was in agreement, and it was too late to call it off, even had we considered it
                    desirable to do so. I told him that on the contrary, I thought that it was a
                    good thing and then read him the first paragraph of Mr. Feely’s telegram No. 126
                    of October 15, 10 a.m., showing that the Chief of the General Staff of the
                    Bolivian army had made suggestions along these same lines to Mr. Feely on the
                    night of October 14. The Minister was much impressed by this and asked me to
                    send him a memorandum regarding it. I told him I would do it.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rancis</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >hite</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
